I see there's already some code that was added (lines 1556-1563). This is a different approach than mine. Let me understand what this code does:

```cpp
if (match(Op0, m_Add(m_And(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C1)),
                     m_And(m_Value(Y), m_SpecificInt(*C1)))) &&
    C1->isPowerOf2() && C1->logBase2() == ShAmtC - 1) {
  Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(X, Y);
  Value *And2 = Builder.CreateAnd(And, ConstantInt::get(Ty, *C1));
  return BinaryOperator::CreateLShr(And2, ConstantInt::get(Ty, ShAmtC - 1));
}
```

This matches `(and X, C1) + (and Y, C1)` where C1 is a power of 2 and `log2(C1) == ShAmtC - 1`. But this doesn't seem right for our case.

